commentTextItems.html: comes down the track and lofts it over long-off for a huge six. That shot ends the match

commentPostTextItems.html: There was a stutter in the middle, but the opening partnership of 100 made that seem insignificant on the day. Dwayne Bravo and Marlon Samuels made sure that they win the game. Dwayne Bravo is the man of the match.
Thanks for joining us today and good night from all of us here

dismissalText.commentary: Kirk Edwards run out (Dockrell) 2 (7b 0x4 0x6) SR: 28.57

dismissalComment.html: comes forward and punches it to mid-on. He sets off for the single and isn't quick enough to beat Dockrell's throw from there

dismissalText.commentary: Darren Bravo c †Wilson b Thompson 1 (9b 0x4 0x6) SR: 11.11

dismissalComment.html: fuller ball outside the off stump. Darren looks to drive and gets a faint edge back to the keeper. That was a loose shot by the man whose style is similar to Brian Lara

dismissalText.commentary: Kieran Powell st †Wilson b Stirling 57 (80b 7x4 0x6) SR: 71.25

dismissalComment.html: fuller ball outside the off stump. Powell skips down the track and looks to loft it away. The angle beats his and he is stumped

dismissalText.commentary: Denesh Ramdin lbw b Dockrell 15 (19b 3x4 0x6) SR: 78.94

dismissalComment.html: fuller ball on the leg stump. Ramdin looks to sweep it and misses. He is struck in front of the middle stump and is gone. Is there a twist in the match?
